OSI-approved open source license.

By accessing, copying, modifying, deploying, or distributing any part of this
repository, you agree to the terms below.

1. Definitions

"Software" means the source code, assets, configuration samples, and
documentation published in this repository.

"Halo Shop Edition" means the paid Halo mall product, or another product or
service expressly authorized in writing by the copyright holder with equivalent
scope.

"Production Use" means making the Software available to actual end users,
customers, merchants, or the general public in a live, usable environment,
including a deployed WeChat Mini Program or any equivalent client.

"Authorized Customer" means a person or entity that has lawfully obtained a
valid license to use Halo Shop Edition.

"Authorized Developer" means an employee or contractor acting on behalf of an
Authorized Customer within the scope of that customer's valid Halo Shop Edition
license.

2. Permitted evaluation and development use

Any person may view, download, copy, run, and modify the Software solely for
evaluation, security review, local development, testing, demonstration, or
client preview in a non-production environment.

3. Production use restriction

Production Use is permitted only by:

(a) an Authorized Customer; or
(b) an Authorized Developer acting for an Authorized Customer.

Any person who does not have a valid Halo Shop Edition license may not use the
Software for Production Use.

4. Customer modification and self-use

An Authorized Customer and its Authorized Developers may copy, modify, build,
deploy, and use the Software as a template for that Authorized Customer's own
projects and environments, to the extent reasonably necessary to develop, test,
operate, and maintain one or more client applications that integrate with that
Authorized Customer's valid Halo Shop Edition environment.

5. No redistribution or resale

Except as expressly permitted by this license, you may not publish, sublicense,
sell, assign, transfer, distribute, or make available the Software or any
modified version of the Software to any third party.

For clarity, the following are not permitted without prior written permission
from the copyright holder:

(a) redistributing this repository or a fork of it;
(b) providing the Software to any third party as a reusable source-code
deliverable, template, starter, or toolkit;
(c) reselling or relicensing the Software;
(d) offering the Software, or a substantially similar derivative of it, as a
competing product.

6. Modification restrictions

You may modify the Software for the permitted uses described in this license.
You may not remove, bypass, or circumvent license checks, payment prompts,
authorization logic, attribution notices, or technical measures that protect
paid products or services of the copyright holder or its affiliates.

7. Separate products and services

This license applies only to the Software published in this repository. It does
not grant any right to use Halo Shop Edition server software, paid plugins,
